# Boost.TypeLayout -- AI Coding Rules

## 1. High-Level Overview

### What This Project Does

Boost.TypeLayout is a **header-only C++ library** that generates compile-time type layout
signatures via C++26 static reflection (P2996). Core question it answers:
"Can struct T be safely `memcpy`'d between endpoint A and endpoint B?"

Two `consteval` functions form the public API:
- `get_layout_signature<T>()` returns a `FixedString` with the full byte-level layout.
- `layout_signatures_match<T, U>()` returns `true` if two types have identical byte layouts.

Signatures are deterministic, human-readable strings.
Example: `[64-le]record[s:16,a:8]{@0:u32[s:4,a:4],@8:f64[s:8,a:8]}`

### Architecture -- Two Layers

```
Core Layer (requires P2996 / C++26)
include/boost/typelayout/
  typelayout.hpp              # Umbrella header
  signature.hpp               # get_layout_signature, layout_signatures_match, get_arch_prefix
  layout_traits.hpp           # layout_traits<T>: signature + has_pointer/padding/opaque/etc.
  fixed_string.hpp            # FixedString<N>: compile-time string, to_fixed_string()
  opaque.hpp                  # TYPELAYOUT_REGISTER_OPAQUE macro
  fwd.hpp                     # Forward declarations, always_false
  config.hpp                  # Configuration macros (endianness)
  detail/
    signature_impl.hpp        # TypeSignature<T>::calculate() -- the core recursive engine
    reflect.hpp               # P2996 reflection helpers (qualified_name_for, has_virtual_base)
    type_map.hpp              # Type -> canonical name (int->i32, double->f64, etc.)
    sig_parser.hpp            # Signature string parser (C++17): sig_has_padding, sig_contains_token

Tools Layer (mostly C++17, some require P2996)
include/boost/typelayout/tools/
  safety_level.hpp            # SafetyLevel enum + classify_signature() -- C++17
  classify.hpp                # classify<T> (compile-time, wraps layout_traits) -- P2996
  serialization_free.hpp      # is_local_serialization_free<T>, SignatureRegistry -- P2996
  sig_export.hpp              # SigExporter, TYPELAYOUT_EXPORT_TYPES -- P2996
  sig_types.hpp               # TypeEntry, PlatformInfo structs (shared) -- C++17
  compat_check.hpp            # CompatReporter (cross-platform diff) -- C++17
  platform_detect.hpp         # Arch/OS/compiler detection macros -- C++17
  detail/foreach.hpp          # Variadic macro helper -- C++17
```

### Code Map -- Key Entry Points

| Task                        | Start here                                                         |
|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
| How signatures are generated | `detail/signature_impl.hpp` -> `TypeSignature<T>::calculate()`    |
| How types are classified     | `detail/reflect.hpp`, `detail/type_map.hpp`                       |
| How layout_traits works      | `layout_traits.hpp` -> `layout_traits<T>` struct                  |
| How padding is detected      | `layout_traits.hpp` -> `compute_has_padding<T>()` (bitmap)        |
| How safety is classified     | `tools/classify.hpp` -> `classify<T>`, `tools/safety_level.hpp`   |
| How opaque types work        | `opaque.hpp` -> macros + `has_opaque_signature` concept           |
| Cross-platform pipeline      | `tools/sig_export.hpp` (Phase 1) -> `tools/compat_check.hpp` (Phase 2) |

