## 2. Code Style & Consistency Enforcers

### 2.1 Absolute Rules

- **No emoji** in code, comments, commit messages, or documentation. Use `[FIXED]`, `[TODO]`, `(!)`.
- **`consteval`, not `constexpr`** for all signature-generating functions. `constexpr` is only for helper utilities.
- **FixedString<N>** with N = exact content length. No slack, no over-allocation.
- **Header-only library** -- no `.cpp` source files in the library. Tests are `.cpp` files.

### 2.2 Naming Conventions

| Element          | Convention                                  | Example                              |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Namespace        | `boost::typelayout`, detail in `boost::typelayout::detail` | `namespace boost { namespace typelayout {` |
| Classes/Structs  | PascalCase                                  | `FixedString`, `SigExporter`, `TypeSignature` |
| Enum classes     | PascalCase                                  | `SafetyLevel::TrivialSafe`           |
| Functions        | snake_case                                  | `get_layout_signature`, `compute_has_padding` |
| Template params  | PascalCase single letters or descriptive    | `<typename T>`, `<std::size_t N>`    |
| Constants        | snake_case or UPPER_SNAKE for macros        | `inline constexpr`, `TYPELAYOUT_REGISTER_OPAQUE` |
| Files            | snake_case.hpp                              | `layout_traits.hpp`, `sig_parser.hpp` |
| Test files       | `test_<descriptive_name>.cpp`               | `test_padding_precision.cpp`         |
| Header guards    | `#ifndef BOOST_TYPELAYOUT_<PATH>_HPP`       | `#ifndef BOOST_TYPELAYOUT_DETAIL_REFLECT_HPP` |

### 2.3 Include Order

1. Project headers (`<boost/typelayout/...>`)
2. Standard library headers (`<cstdint>`, `<type_traits>`, etc.)
3. Test utilities (in test files only: `"test_util.hpp"`)

### 2.4 File Header Standard

Library headers require a copyright block:
```cpp
// Copyright (c) 2024-2026 TypeLayout Development Team
// Distributed under the Boost Software License, Version 1.0.
```
Test files do NOT require a copyright header.

### 2.5 Comment Style

- Concise, 1-2 line comments preferred. Avoid multi-paragraph explanations.
- Use `//` for inline comments, not `/* */`.
- BNF grammar specs in `signature_impl.hpp` are the exception -- keep them complete.
- `static_assert` messages serve as inline documentation -- make them descriptive.

### 2.6 Commit Message Format

```
type: description
```
Valid types: `fix:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `perf:`, `feat:`, `refactor:`

