## 3. Rapid Reference & Context Map

### 3.1 Core API Signatures (Top 10)

```cpp
// -- Signature generation (consteval, P2996) --
template <typename T>
[[nodiscard]] consteval auto get_layout_signature() noexcept;
  // Returns: FixedString with arch prefix + full layout signature

template <typename T1, typename T2>
[[nodiscard]] consteval bool layout_signatures_match() noexcept;
  // Returns: true if T1 and T2 have identical byte-level layouts

[[nodiscard]] consteval auto get_arch_prefix() noexcept;
  // Returns: FixedString "[64-le]", "[64-be]", "[32-le]", or "[32-be]"

// -- Layout traits (consteval struct, P2996) --
template <typename T> struct layout_traits {
    static constexpr auto signature;          // FixedString
    static constexpr bool has_pointer;
    static constexpr bool has_bit_field;
    static constexpr bool has_opaque;
    static constexpr bool is_platform_variant;
    static constexpr bool has_padding;
    static constexpr std::size_t field_count;
    static constexpr std::size_t total_size;
    static constexpr std::size_t alignment;
};

// -- Safety classification (consteval, P2996) --
template <typename T> struct classify { static constexpr SafetyLevel value; };
template <typename T> inline constexpr SafetyLevel classify_v;

// -- Runtime classification (constexpr, C++17) --
constexpr SafetyLevel classify_signature(std::string_view sig) noexcept;
constexpr bool sig_has_padding(std::string_view sig) noexcept;
constexpr bool sig_contains_token(std::string_view haystack, std::string_view needle) noexcept;

// -- Serialization-free check (P2996 + runtime) --
template <typename T> inline constexpr bool is_local_serialization_free_v;
template <typename T> bool is_transfer_safe(std::string_view remote_sig);

// -- Opaque registration macro --
TYPELAYOUT_REGISTER_OPAQUE(Type, Tag, HasPointer)
  // Must be inside namespace boost::typelayout
```

### 3.2 Key Constants & Enums

```cpp
// SafetyLevel (ordered best=0 to worst=4)
enum class SafetyLevel {
    TrivialSafe     = 0,  // Safe for memcpy + cross-platform
    PaddingRisk     = 1,  // Has padding (info-leak risk)
    PlatformVariant = 2,  // wchar_t / f80 / bit-fields differ across platforms
    PointerRisk     = 3,  // Contains pointers; memcpy produces dangling refs
    Opaque          = 4,  // Unanalyzable; user must verify manually
};
```

### 3.3 Signature Format Grammar

```
Arch prefix:   [BITS-ENDIAN]            e.g. [64-le], [32-be]
Record:        record[s:SIZE,a:ALIGN]{@OFFSET:TYPE[s:SIZE,a:ALIGN],...}
Padding:       pad:N                    N padding bytes at given offset
Opaque:        O(Tag|SIZE|ALIGN)        via TYPELAYOUT_REGISTER_OPAQUE
Opaque container: O(Tag|SIZE|ALIGN)<elem_sig>    via TYPELAYOUT_OPAQUE_CONTAINER_RELOCATABLE
Opaque map:       O(Tag|SIZE|ALIGN)<key,val>     via TYPELAYOUT_OPAQUE_MAP_RELOCATABLE
Array:         TYPE[N]                  fixed-size array, element type recursed
Bit-field:     @BYTE.BIT:bits<WIDTH,UNDERLYING_TYPE>
```

### 3.4 Type Name Mappings (type_map.hpp)

| C++ type         | Signature token | C++ type       | Signature token |
|------------------|-----------------|----------------|-----------------|
| `int8_t`         | `i8`            | `uint8_t`      | `u8`            |
| `int16_t`        | `i16`           | `uint16_t`     | `u16`           |
| `int32_t`        | `i32`           | `uint32_t`     | `u32`           |
| `int64_t`        | `i64`           | `uint64_t`     | `u64`           |
| `float`          | `f32`           | `double`       | `f64`           |
| `long double`    | `f80`           | `bool`         | `bool`          |
| `char`           | `char`          | `wchar_t`      | `wchar`         |
| `char8_t`        | `c8`            | `char16_t`     | `c16`           |
| `char32_t`       | `c32`           | `void*`        | `ptr`           |
| `T(*)()`         | `fnptr`         | `T C::*`       | `memptr`        |
| `T&`             | `ref`           | `T&&`          | `rref`          |

