## 4. Architecture Invariants (NEVER violate)

### 4.1 Layer Separation

- **Tools layer C++17 files** must NOT `#include` any Core headers that use P2996.
- C++17-only files: `safety_level.hpp`, `compat_check.hpp`, `sig_types.hpp`, `platform_detect.hpp`, `detail/foreach.hpp`, `detail/sig_parser.hpp`.
- P2996-required tools: `classify.hpp`, `serialization_free.hpp`, `sig_export.hpp`.

### 4.2 Dual-Path Padding Detection

Two independent implementations detect padding. They MUST agree:
1. `compute_has_padding<T>()` -- compile-time byte-coverage bitmap via P2996 reflection (in `layout_traits.hpp`)
2. `sig_has_padding()` -- runtime string parser (in `detail/sig_parser.hpp`)

A `static_assert` in `layout_traits<T>` enforces consistency. **NEVER** update one path without updating the other.

### 4.3 Virtual Inheritance Rejection

`signature_impl.hpp` rejects types with virtual bases at compile time via `static_assert`. Virtual bases introduce hidden vbptrs and diamond double-counting. This is intentional and must never be relaxed.

### 4.4 Opaque Registration Order

Opaque types must be registered BEFORE any `get_layout_signature<T>()` call that encounters them. Registration is done inside `namespace boost::typelayout`.

### 4.5 Flattening Invariant

Struct field names and inheritance hierarchy are erased. Only byte-level identity is preserved. Two structs with different field names but identical byte layout MUST produce identical signatures.

### 4.6 Array Element Recursion

`type_has_opaque` and `compute_has_padding` MUST recurse into array element types via `std::remove_all_extents_t<T>`. Failure to do so causes false negatives.

